<ITEM>Chap. XXXIV. An epidemic fever rages among us&mdash;we abandon our conque&s;ts&mdash;I am &s;eized with the di&s;tem|per; write a petition to the captain, which is rejected&mdash;I am in danger of &s;uffocation through the malice of Crampley, and relieved by a &s;erjeant&mdash;my &s;ever in|crea&s;es&mdash;the chaplain wants to confe&s;s me&mdash;I obtain a favourable cri&s;is&mdash;Morgan's affection for me proved&mdash;the behaviour of Mac&s;hane and Crampley towards me&mdash;Captain Oakhum is removed into another &s;hip with his beloved doctor&mdash;our new captain de&s;cribed&mdash;an adventure of Morgan, 208</ITEM>
<ITEM>Chap. XXXV. Captain Whiffle &s;ends for me&mdash;his &s;ituati|on de&s;cribed&mdash;his &s;urgeon arrives, pre&s;cribes for him, and puts him to bed&mdash;a bed is put up for Mr. Simper con|tiguous to the &s;tate-room, which, with other parts of the captain's behaviour, gives the &s;hip's company a very unfavourable idea of their commander&mdash;I am detained in the We&s;t-Indies by the admiral, and go on board of the Lizard &s;loop of war in quality of &s;urgeon's mate, where I make my&s;elf known to the &s;urgeon, who treats me very kindly&mdash;I go on &s;hore, &s;ell my ticket, pur|cha&s;e nece&s;&s;aries, and, at my return on board, am &s;ur|pri&s;ed at the &s;ight of Crampley, who is appointed <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> &s;loop&mdash;we &s;ail on a cruize&mdash;take a prize, in which I arrive at Port Morant under the command of my me&s;s-mate, with whom I live in great harmony, 217</ITEM>
<ITEM>Chap. XXXVI. A &s;trange adventure in con&s;equence of which I am extremely happy&mdash;Crampley does me ill offices with the captain; but his malice is defeated by the good nature and friend&s;hip of the &s;urgeon&mdash;we re|turn to Port-<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">oyal&mdash;our captain gets the command of a larger &s;hip, and is &s;ucceeded by an old man&mdash;Brayl is provided for&mdash;we receive orders to &s;ail for England, 222</ITEM>
</LIST>
